ATTENTION PARENTS:

Request for transportation is to be completed by June 4 in order to not have to wait on busing for the 2020-2021 school year! As you drop your computers off next week bring in a Proof of residency that is current and no more than 60 days old! This includes but not limited to ( bank statement, paystub, billing statement, lease/mortgage, etc.) If you wait you will be put on the back end of the list and a waiting period!

Call in to the school today to schedule a time to come in! 330-752-2766

post_text:
This week we will be handing out supply bags that contain: summer bridge books, notebooks, and pencils. Parents will be able to get a chromebook if they need one also. Lunch pickup will be available as well! We will be in the building on Mon. & Tues. from 9 -2 and Wed. 3-5pm. We will be making our deliveries to those who are not able to get to the school, parents must answer the door if they wish to receive a chrome book. This week teachers are making sure students know how to log in and get to the online E-learning programs set in forth by our teachers!

We have been very hard at work during this time making sure all students are still engaged in their education! We give thanks to all parents for your patience during this time!

Good Afternoon. If you have not heard Governor Dewine has extended the mandatory school closure until May 1st, with this announcement there are several things that parents and students need to be aware of.

The expectation during this school closure is that all students should be working on online lessons or through a paper packet. If students are not, or do not complete these lessons they are at putting themselves in jeopardy to receive zeros for all work assigned.

Due to the extension of the school closure we will be distributing additional work and food to students on Monday, April 6th and Tuesday, April 7th. Students have the option of doing online or paper packet, just like they did for‚Ä¶
